{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b735935-43f4-456d-a7ac-2b984391a472","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer.** In 3.x the SDK bundled the VSTest adapter bridge alongside Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so `vstest.console` could still discover tests. In 4.x, only Microsoft.Testing.Platform is included — `vstest.console` sees no tests because there's no adapter for it.\n\n**Two options to fix:**\n\n1. **Migrate your CI away from `vstest.console`** (recommended):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively in .NET 9+\n   # or run the test exe directly:\n   ./TestProject        # Microsoft.Testing.Platform built-in runner\n   ```\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest adapter bridge** in your project:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableVSTestAdapter>true</EnableVSTestAdapter>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This restores the bridge so `vstest.console` can discover tests again, but it's considered a backward-compatibility shim — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the path forward.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"29da74f2-448d-453a-a588-7cac96bc0761","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a breaking change when upgrading from MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0 to MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0, specifically related to test discovery with vstest.console. This is a knowledge question about MSTest SDK changes.\n\nLet me look at the files in the current directory to understand context, but this is primarily a knowledge-based question.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.0+, there was a shift toward Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner. In MSTest.Sdk 3.x, both VSTest and Microsoft.Testing.Platform were supported, and you could opt in/out. \n\n\nIn version 4.0 and later, the VSTest adapter was removed by default, which is the breaking change—`vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests without explicitly opting back in, whereas in 3.x it was included and available.\n\nTo resolve this, the user can either switch to running tests directly with the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner, or re-enable VSTest compatibility by adding the adapter package or setting the appropriate property in the project file to restore that functionality.","outputTokens":912,"requestId":"E3C5:AB6AD:244B1C7:283E9B7:6A053F78"},"id":"eef8ef7d-ab18-4eba-933f-d339d09d2843","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:20:44.517Z","parentId":"2e85df1f-aaf6-40be-bd1b-25f3bbdaa42c"}
